schema.text: AC dat object definitions / documentation. Heavily based off of ACE.DatReader FileTypes

enum.name: SkillId
enum.text: The Skill identifies a specific Character skill.

enum.name: AttributeId
enum.text: The AttributeId identifies a specific Character attribute.

enum.name: VitalId
enum.text: The VitalId identifies a specific Character vital (secondary attribute).

type.name: Stab
type.text: Information about a static object spawn.

field.name: Id
field.text: The id of this static object

field.name: Frame
field.text: The position information

field.name: Origin
field.text: The origin, offset from the parent

field.name: Orientation
field.text: The orientation

field.name: ModelId
field.text: Either a SetupModel or GfxObj id.

field.name: Frame
field.text: The position information

field.name: Blue
field.text: The blue amount from 0-255

field.name: Green
field.text: The green amount from 0-255

field.name: Red
field.text: The red amount from 0-255

field.name: Alpha
field.text: The alpha amount from 0-255

field.name: Name
field.text: The name of the spell

field.name: Description
field.text: The description of the spell

field.name: School
field.text: The magic school the spell belongs to

field.name: Icon
field.text: The data id of the spell icon

field.name: Category
field.text: Spell category

field.name: Duration
field.text: This is only set when MetaSpellType is SpellType.Enchantment | SpellType.FellowEnchantment.

field.name: DegradeModifier
field.text: This is only set when MetaSpellType is SpellType.Enchantment | SpellType.FellowEnchantment.

field.name: DegradeLimit
field.text: This is only set when MetaSpellType is SpellType.Enchantment | SpellType.FellowEnchantment.

field.name: PortalLifetime
field.text: This is only set when MetaSpellType is SpellType.PortalSummon.

vector.name: RawComponents
vector.text: This should always be a length of 8.

field.name: DeviceIndex
field.text: The index of the device to use

field.name: Key
field.text: Keyboard Device / Mouse Device Enumeration (DIK_ / DIMOFS_)

field.name: Modifiers
field.text: Flags that determine what modifier/meta keys are defined for this binding. These correspond to KeyMap.MetaKeys.

field.name: ActionName
field.text: These correspond to 0x2200002B enum dat entry

type.name: SkillFormula
type.text: Formula that dictates how to calculate a skill `(Attribute1 + Attribute2?) / Divisor`.

field.name: HasSecondAttribute
field.text: True if this formula uses a second attribute for the calculation

field.name: UseFormula
field.text: If this is false, dont use this formula just use the base value of the skill

field.name: Divisor
field.text: The divisor used in the formula.

field.name: Attribute1
field.text: The first attribute to use

field.name: Attribute2
field.text: The second attribute to use. Only valid if HasSecondAttribute is true

type.name: StartingArea
type.text: Information about a starting area available during character creation

type.name: Position
type.text: Information about an ingame position containing a cell id and a frame

field.name: CellId
field.text: The full id of the landcell

type.name: HeritageGroupCG
type.text: Information about a heritage group, used during character creation

field.name: SetupId
field.text: Basic character model

field.name: EnvironmentSetupId
field.text: This is the background environment used during character creation

field.name: AttributeCredits
field.text: Starting attribute credits

field.name: SkillCredits
field.text: Starting skill credits

field.name: Type
field.text: This seems to always be TextureType.Texture2D in the dats.

type.name: RenderSurface
type.text: This holds raw texture data. DB_TYPE_RENDERSURFACE in the client.

field.name: Width
field.text: The width of the SurfaceTexture

field.name: Height
field.text: The height of the SurfaceTexture

field.name: Format
field.text: The format of the SourceData

vector.name: SourceData
vector.text: The source data of the texture

field.name: DefaultPaletteId
field.text: This is only set when Format is PixelFormat.PFID_INDEX16 | PixelFormat.PFID_P8.

field.name: Name
field.text: The name of the keymap

vector.name: StartingAreas
vector.text: A list of starting areas available during character creation

type.name: ExperienceTable
type.text: Holds the experience required for different attributes/vitals/skill/levels, as well as the amount of skill credits obtained for each level. DB_TYPE_XP_TABLE_0 in the client.

vector.name: Attributes
vector.text: The amount of experience required to train attributes

vector.name: Vitals
vector.text: The amount of experience required to train vitals

vector.name: TrainedSkills
vector.text: The amount of experience required to train trained skills

vector.name: SpecializedSkills
vector.text: The amount of experience required to train specialized skills

vector.name: Levels
vector.text: The amount of experience required to level a character

vector.name: SkillCredits
vector.text: The amount of skill credits per level

type.name: LandBlockInfo
type.text: Stores static spawns, buildings. DB_TYPE_LBI in the client.

field.name: NumCells
field.text: The number of inside cells. These can be looked up at 0xAAAABBBB where AAAA is the landblock id and BBBB is the cell id + 0x100

vector.name: Surfaces
vector.text: A list of surface ids. These are not fully qualified so you need to or with 0x08000000 to get the file id.

field.name: EnvironmentId
field.text: The environment id. This is not fully qualified so you need to or with 0x0D000000 to get the file id.

vector.name: VisibleCells
vector.text: A list of visible cell ids
